  <body id="msgFeedSummaryBody" selected="false">
    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>Multistep forms are a great improvement to the user experience, especially if a form has a lot of fields. The problem is, when you have required fields on a particular step, and the field is not filled in, the user will get a validation error when hitting back. But fear not. You can still have your nice multistep form and get rid of these pesky errors when hitting a back button. The problem is solved by adding the <em>#limit_validation_errors</em> property to the back button.</p>
